        detentiongirl "If we rush in there, and something happens then we don't ever get to the bottom of this."
        mc "(Wow, out of all of us she is the one who is slowing down?)"
        $ sandstorm_pose = "bridgemdialogue5"
        mc "Emma is right, we have to wait out the storm."
        mc "It is annoying though... Especially since the clerk wasn't exactly helpful either."
        $ sandstorm_pose = "bridgemdialogue6"
        detentiongirl "What did he say?"
        $ sandstorm_pose = "bridgemdialogue5"
        mc "Nothing, he avoided and denied all of it."
        mc "Then he looked like he was disengaging but... as if he was thinking about something, or worrying."
        $ sandstorm_pose = "bridgemdialogue6"
        bffsis "I hate that guy, gives me the creeps."
        detentiongirl "So, now what?"
        mc "I'm not sure, I was hoping you guys would know of a plan B..."
        $ sandstorm_pose = "bridgemdialogue3"
        detentiongirl "I don't know either, if only there was some kind of way past this sandstorm..."
        $ sandstorm_pose = "bridgemdialogue7"
        detentiongirl "Or maybe... If we all hide behind Bridgette she can let her chest absorb most of the impact."
        $ sandstorm_pose = "bridgemdialogue8"
        bffsis "Very funny, Emma."
        bffsis "Jealousy is a real bitch, isn't she?"
        "They joke around for a moment, the three of you have no choice but to wait impatiently for the storm to subdue."
        $ sandstorm_pose = "bridgemdialogue5"
        mc "I guess we can come back later."
        $ sandstorm_pose = ""
        scene black with slow_fade
        hide screen tempbunkerscreen
        $ questlog.EndQuest(quest_visitbunker)
        $ questlog.StartQuest(quest_waitoutstorm)
        pause 0.5
        return
    elif quest_waitoutstorm in questlog.quest_list:
        mc "(Oh no, the storm is still raging out there.)"
        mc "(Sandstorms usually don't last this long, I wonder what the hell is going on here.)"
        $ sandstorm_pose = "bridgemdialogue1"
        bffsis "Hey [name]."
        mc "Hey guys, I guess we're out of luck huh?"
        $ sandstorm_pose = "bridgemdialogue3"
        detentiongirl "This isn't normal for a storm like this, it was supposed to calm down last night."
        mc "I know, I've been wondering the same thing."
        mc "It's curious how it seems to stay in one area too, not closing in or moving away."
        jump militarycrash
    else:
        return

